Revision history for DBIO-DB2

{{$NEXT}}
    - Introspect: capture GENERATED AS IDENTITY in column metadata so
      is_auto_increment is exposed to DBIO::Generate
    - Introspect: drop 6 redundant contract methods (table_keys, table_columns,
      table_columns_info, table_pk_info, table_uniq_info, table_is_view);
      inherited unchanged from DBIO::Introspect::Base since the native model
      already uses the canonical shape
    - Introspect: use _aggregate_by_ordered for FK grouping; keep DB2-specific
      parent-PK resolution
    - Introspect: fix unique_rule->uniquerule typo and tag the PK-backing
      index with origin=>'pk' so the inherited table_uniq_info drops it
    - Diff::Table/Column/Index: adopt DBIO::Diff::Op base + mk_diff_accessors,
      replace inline 'did this change?' checks with is_same_column /
      is_same_index from DBIO::Diff::Compare
    - Deploy: adopt DBIO::Deploy::Base; install/diff/apply/upgrade come from
      the shared base, this class supplies _ddl_class/_introspect_class/
      _diff_class hooks and the DB2-specific _build_target_model that splices
      the desired schema into a throwaway CREATE SCHEMA
    - Tests: consolidate byte-identical t/10-db2.t + t/20-db2-core.t into
      t/10-db2.t (the single integration test)
    - DDL: emit CREATE VIEW for non-virtual views (from view_definition),
      after all tables; previously view sources got a CREATE TABLE
    - Initial extraction from DBIO core as separate distribution
    - Remove sql_limit_dialect method (DBIO core uses apply_limit now)
    - TODO: SQLMaker needs apply_limit with RowNumberOver/FetchFirst dialect
